  "markup": "\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\u0022\u003EAbout 80 percent of adults experience low back pain (LBP) at some point in their lifetime. It is the most common cause of job-related disability and a leading contributor to missed workdays. Most LBP is acute or short-term and can last days or a few weeks.\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cbr /\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\u0022\u003EMost sources of a patient\u0027s LBP have a mechanical disruption as the root cause, but only the symptoms of pain, inflammation, and muscle spasms are addressed with pharmacological agents. Photobiomodulation (PBM) has shown to be an effective evidence-based addition to your clinical practice.\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cbr /\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\u0022\u003EJoin Dr. Christopher Carraway as he discusses the multifaceted approach to managing low back pain. From start to finish, combining active and passive care with physical medicine and PBM can yield superior outcomes for low back pain patients.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cbr /\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\u0022\u003EKey Talking Points\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre; font-family: tahoma;\u0022\u003E - Research review on treating low back pain with PBM\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre; font-family: tahoma;\u0022\u003E - Integrating PBM into current treatment strategies for enhanced outcomes\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre; font-family: tahoma;\u0022\u003E - Protocols you can implement today to find relief for acute and chronic patients\u0026nbsp;\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E"
}]]></Value>
    </description>
